Subject: Re: [VB] Steam Clean an Engine?

If you do run a cleaner through your engine, do change the oil a couple 
hundred miles after wards, w/o heavy driving in that time.   sludge broke loose 
inside can clog things up.  Just like with a motor that sat for years.

I do a pressure wash every so often to keep the engine and compartment clean, 
to aid cooling of the engine and make it pleasanter to work on,

A very clean engine does get start to corrode on the outside (white stuff) on 
the case.  Well, it happened to my bug, nothing major, but I spray the case 
w/ liquid wrench after cleaning as it gets and stays too clean.  (Bet you never 
heard that one before)


